  "settingsPrivacyPolicyTitle": "Privacy Policy",
  "settingsPrivacyPolicySubtitle": "Review what the app processes and how it is stored.",
  "privacyPolicyTitle": "Privacy Policy",
  "privacyPolicySummary": "This document explains what information the current app implementation processes on your device and through external services.",
  "privacyPolicyLastUpdatedLabel": "Last updated",
  "privacyPolicyLastUpdatedValue": "2026-03-08",
  "privacyPolicyDataTitle": "1. Information processed",
  "privacyPolicyDataBody": "The app may process settings data (theme, language, onboarding state), check-in data (mood, energy, note, timestamp), safety-plan data (warning signs, coping steps, reasons to stay safe, emergency steps), trusted-contact data (name, relationship, phone number, primary status), location data when you search nearby clinics, and technical logs used for error handling.",
  "privacyPolicyPurposeTitle": "2. Why the data is used",
  "privacyPolicyPurposeBody": "This information is used to provide the screening flow, show result guidance, save check-ins and safety plans, search nearby clinics, launch phone or directions actions, keep theme and language settings, render ads on non-critical screens, and investigate failures.",
  "privacyPolicyStorageTitle": "3. Storage and retention",
  "privacyPolicyStorageBody": "On mobile and desktop builds, data is stored in the local Isar database. On web builds, data is stored in browser localStorage. The app does not create a default account backend, so most information stays on your device.",
  "privacyPolicySharingTitle": "4. External transfers and third parties",
  "privacyPolicySharingBody": "When you run nearby-clinic search, your current location and search radius may be sent to the configured Overpass endpoint. If you tap phone or directions actions, control moves to the operating system or another app and that platform's policies apply. Screening answers, check-ins, safety plans, and trusted contacts are not uploaded to a default server.",
  "privacyPolicyAdsTitle": "5. Ads and external SDKs",
  "privacyPolicyAdsBody": "When ads are enabled, Google Mobile Ads SDK may process ad requests. Based on the current repository, no separate user-behavior analytics SDK was found, but advertising providers may still process technical information under their own policies.",
  "privacyPolicySecurityTitle": "6. Security",
  "privacyPolicySecurityBody": "The app uses structured logging and masking logic to reduce direct exposure of sensitive values. Even so, local data may still be exposed on shared devices, lost devices, or compromised systems.",
  "privacyPolicyControlTitle": "7. Your choices",
  "privacyPolicyControlBody": "You can deny location permission and the app will fall back to a default clinic list. You can add, remove, or reprioritize trusted contacts in the app. There is currently no dedicated full-data erase flow, so full deletion may require uninstalling the app or clearing browser storage.",
  "privacyPolicyContactTitle": "8. Contact and notice",
  "privacyPolicyContactBody": "This repository does not currently embed an operator support contact. Before external release, publish a support contact and the latest policy link in your store listing or support page.",
